<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,834,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males are easily distinguished from known congeners by shape of procursus (
<figureCitation box="[1195,1282,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
; distinctively widened and strongly curved distal element, much smaller than in similar species, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1122,1251,871,894]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[1122,1251,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1266,1391,870,895]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maraba">
<emphasis box="[1266,1391,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. maraba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoblechroscelis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. pseudoblechroscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Machado" authorityYear="2007" box="[391,537,906,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis box="[391,537,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); also by armature of male chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[978,1110,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 50–51</figureCitation>
; distinctive undulating shape of apophyses in lateral view), by shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[755,885,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 52–53</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[897,971,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–77" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1508,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 69–77. Female epigyna in ventral and lateral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelis group (part 2). 69–71. M. amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 72–74. M. jamari sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18954).75–77.M.tapajos sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18958)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202537/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">69–70</figureCitation>
; large median depression, lateral margins diverging toward anterior, bordered posteriorly by large pocket; pair of conical lateral processes; very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Machado" authorityYear="2007" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but median pocket reaching further back in lateral view), and by female internal genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1387,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 54</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1400,1431,1015,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–77" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1508,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 69–77. Female epigyna in ventral and lateral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelis group (part 2). 69–71. M. amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 72–74. M. jamari sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18954).75–77.M.tapajos sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18958)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202537/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">71</figureCitation>
; similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[269,396,1050,1075]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maraba">
<emphasis box="[269,396,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. maraba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Machado" authorityYear="2007" box="[456,605,1050,1075]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis box="[456,605,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; pore-plates larger and slightly curved towards posterior) (female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoblechroscelis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. pseudoblechroscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unknown).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
